Description: Handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp; leaf symbol.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.51, 16. Name, Armosilas. Probably from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum ABC0092.11.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0681)
